#This the file defining unified color theme for any interactive shell environment, so I have a nice, clear and unified view of my shell from anywhere.
#It is supposed to run in a color-free environment (all color-related possible variables should be removed prior to running this script, but some important ones are nevertheless removed for security here.
#The color-scheme is defined for 8-color compatible terminals (like the linux tty defaults ones), 256-color compatible terminals (almost every actual terminal emulators issued from or after xterm), and for RGB-color compatible terminals (if any???).

#Force important colors variables reset


#Detect the type of terminal
case "$TERM" in
	linux) supported=0;;	
	256) supported=1;;
	all) supported=2;;
esac
